<subSubSection pageId="121" pageNumber="122" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="121.[151,1437,356,994]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,573,599]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Ecology</emphasis>
. Largely intertidal; on exposed muddy banks of brackish mangrove swamps, dwelling in burrows and depressions in mud; also under rocks in muddy-rocky intertidal, close to waterfalls or creeks (
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G." box="[1206,1431,608,635]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref72307" refString="Gore, R. H. &amp; Abele, L. G. (1976) Shallow water porcelain crabs from the Pacific coast of Panama and adjacent Caribbean waters (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 237, 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.237" type="journal article" year="1976">Gore &amp; Abele 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hiller, A. &amp; Lazarus, J. F. &amp; Werding, B." box="[151,346,644,671]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" refId="ref73488" refString="Hiller, A., Lazarus, J. F. &amp; Werding, B. (2004) New records and range extensions for porcellanid crabs in the eastern Pacific (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). In: Hendrickx, M. E. (Ed.), Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans. Vol. 3. Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, Universidad de Mexico / UNAM, Ciudad de Mexico, pp. 1 - 12." type="book" year="2004">
Hiller 
<emphasis box="[223,280,644,670]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
; present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="121" pageNumber="122" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="121.[151,1437,356,994]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,681,707]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1968" box="[325,532,680,706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zacae">
<emphasis box="[325,532,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Petrolisthes zacae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[841,974,680,706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[841,974,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. robsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gibbes" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[991,1114,681,706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[991,1114,681,706]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[1174,1277,680,706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilii">
<emphasis box="[1174,1277,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. nobilii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing with them the carapace not transversely striate; the P1 carpus with teeth on mesial margin; and the P2–P4 meri dorsally armed with spines. According to the molecular analysis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hiller, A. &amp; Kraus, H. &amp; Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B." box="[804,1015,752,779]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" pagination="547 - 569" refId="ref73577" refString="Hiller, A., Kraus, H., Almon, M. &amp; Werding, B. (2006) The Petrolisthes galathinus complex: species boundaries based on color pattern, morphology and molecules, and evolutionary interrelationships between the complex and other Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 40, 547 - 569. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2006.03.030" type="journal article" year="2006">
Hiller 
<emphasis box="[876,931,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1968" box="[1025,1116,753,778]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zacae">
<emphasis box="[1025,1116,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. zacae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[1243,1373,752,778]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[1243,1373,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. robsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the eastern Pacific and western Atlantic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gibbes" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[602,721,789,814]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[602,721,789,814]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
representing in turn their sister clade. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1968" box="[1153,1357,788,814]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zacae">
<emphasis box="[1153,1357,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Petrolisthes zacae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1945" box="[215,347,824,850]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robsonae">
<emphasis box="[215,347,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. robsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gibbes" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[363,485,825,850]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[363,485,825,850]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[543,646,824,850]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilii">
<emphasis box="[543,646,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. nobilii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the P2–P4 dactyli: long and slender, with a “thumblike” projection about halfway along ventral (lower) margin, tipped with a movable corneous spinule. This peculiar structure of the ambulatory dactylus is unique within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[747,880,896,922]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,880,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Petrolisthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and likely represents some form of adaptation for living in muddy coditions, i.e. for walking on soft mud (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[778,901,932,959]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref72890" refString="Haig, J. (1968) Eastern Pacific expeditions of the New York Zoological Society. Porcellanid crabs (Crustacea: Anomura) from the west coast of tropical America. Zoologica, New York, 53 (2), 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1968">Haig 1968</bibRefCitation>
). The colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1968" box="[1163,1254,933,958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zacae">
<emphasis box="[1163,1254,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">P. zacae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1269,1363,932,958]" captionStart="FIGURE 76" captionStartId="122.[151,250,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-19@122.[151,1435,181,1943]" captionTargetPageId="122" captionText="FIGURE 76. Petrolisthes zacae Haig, 1968: A–C, extra-limital specimen, male (cl 4.7 mm, cw 4.2 mm) from Bahía Málaga, Colombia (CRBM-UV-cr:2009-103), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontal (C) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532400/files/figure.png" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Figs. 76</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1373,1402,933,959]" captionStart="FIGURE 77" captionStartId="123.[151,250,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,199,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-19@123.[151,1435,199,1728]" captionTargetPageId="123" captionText="FIGURE 77. Petrolisthes zacae Haig, 1968: A, B, extra-limital specimen, female (cl 5.9 mm, cw 6.0 mm) from Bahía Málaga, Colombia (CRBM-UV-cr:2009-103), dorsal (A) and frontal (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532402/files/figure.png" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">77</figureCitation>
) is illustrated for the first time.
</paragraph>
